Wednesday August 28th 2013 1:08 am -04:00,As stated in the video:Python will choose  (single quote) or  (couble quote) depending both on how the string is created and whether an escape sequence is used. The strings are considered to be the same: the markers or delimeters are only to mark values as strings.If the string contains a single quote either delimited out or not it will be returned with double quotes. Conversely if the string contains a double quote Python will return it in single quotes. The behavior is dependent on the content. If the string contains both a single AND double quote then... well things get interesting! >>> test = The girl\s mom said No.>>> testThe girl\s mom said No.But I am only on the second video so Im sure that will be covered shortly ;), Resolved,0
